{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1612300545,"nonce":"BgFJXjPpCctTxZikvf2yhtQ/S08=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU3OTk2OTU0ODE=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/3457","origin":"github"},"title":"\"Convert, Merge, Randomize BAM datasets\" v2.4.0.0 lost the option to input multiple datasets for the merge function","message":"_If this is a duplicate ticket, please combine it. Didn't find this reported yet but could have missed it._\n\n* **Tool:** https://toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/view/devteam/bamtools/4d343c1f606b\n\nThe tool help is outdated as well (doesn't match the tool form -- the prior version or this version).\n\nLooks like the type of \"select\" function(s) incorporated needs to be changed. The tool has several options, running on both multiple datasets (as distinct jobs) and multiple datasets (combined into a single job) should be supported.\n\n* **Tool help (both versions)**\n\n\u003cimg width=\"828\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-02-02 at 12 56 54 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8999735/106661951-ad0f8380-6556-11eb-95d2-e65114c2e121.png\"\u003e\n\n* **The prior version** accepts multiple bam inputs and runs the tool on all in a single job (what is needed for a \"merge\")\n\n\u003cimg width=\"833\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-02-02 at 12 57 15 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8999735/106661977-b13ba100-6556-11eb-8b3b-57272ab5241e.png\"\u003e\n\n* **The current version** accepts multiple bam inputs (selected datasets, or a collection) **BUT** runs the tool on each dataset separately. No way to \"merge\". \n\n\u003cimg width=\"831\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-02-02 at 12 56 39 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8999735/106661999-b698eb80-6556-11eb-8b2a-dff5dbc294a8.png\"\u003e\n\n\u003cimg width=\"835\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-02-02 at 1 08 26 PM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8999735/106662924-e0064700-6557-11eb-8e97-a72355e218e7.png\"\u003e","files":null}]}